### Order API Tests

### 1. Get All Orders
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Get Orders by User ID
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/orders?user_id=1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 3. Get Orders by Status
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/orders?status=pending
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4. Get Orders by User and Status
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/orders?user_id=1&status=paid
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 5. Create New Order
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "user_id": 1,
    "payment_method": "card",
    "items": [
        {
            "product_id": 1,
            "variant_id": null,
            "quantity": 2
        },
        {
            "product_id": 2,
            "variant_id": 5,
            "quantity": 1
        }
    ]
}

